{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-09-11-how-to-change-border-style-in-react-js/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To change border style in react js, you can set  in . It will change border style in react js. Today, I am going to show‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To change border style in react js, you can set <code class=\"language-text\">border: 2px dashed red;</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">BorderDiv</code>. It will change border style in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to change border style in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h2>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h2>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 2: Import react component.</h2>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> styled <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'styled-components'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 3: Create a Component.</h2>\n<p>You can use <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;BorderDiv></code> to change border style in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>BorderDiv<span class=\"token operator\">></span>This has a red dashed border<span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>BorderDiv<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Change border style example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">'styled-components'</code> and set  <code class=\"language-text\">border: 2px dashed red;</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">BorderDiv</code> to change border style in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> styled <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'styled-components'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> BorderDiv <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> styled<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>div<span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">\n  border: 2px dashed red;\n  padding: 10px;\n</span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">App</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>BorderDiv<span class=\"token operator\">></span>This has a red dashed border<span class=\"token operator\">!</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>BorderDiv<span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">border: 2px dashed red;</code> to change border style in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2c447c19f114363c02e03ed835683859/ec897/change-border-style.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 20.253164556962027%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRj4AAABXRUJQVlA4IDIAAADQAQCdASoUAAQAAsBMJZwBTAA9DthE0AD+9Qf6NfEr19n1Mvnlr0bI63xFd9HzvVUAAA=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, change, border, style\"\n        title=\"React, change, border, style\"\n        src=\"/static/2c447c19f114363c02e03ed835683859/8aab1/change-border-style.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/s